Coal Output in China’s Shanxi Province Climbs 18%, Interfax Says

-- B y   A l i s t a i r   H o l l o w a y
-- 
2011-05-26T06:55:23Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-26/coal-output-in-china-s-shanxi-province-climbs-18-interfax-says.html
China ’s Shanxi province mined 256
million metric tons of coal in the first four months of 2011, an
18 percent increase from a year earlier, Interfax reported,
citing provincial government statistics.  Shanxi’s coal output in 2010 was 740 million tons, making
it China’s second-largest coal-producing region after  Inner
Mongolia , Interfax reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alistair Holloway in London at 
 aholloway1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Claudia Carpenter at 
 ccarpenter2@bloomberg.net . 